Today we will start with the box modle in CSS.

#Box Model Components

|-----------------------------------------|
|               Margin                    |
|  |-------------------------------|      |
|  |           Border              |      |
|  |   |-----------------------|   |      |
|  |   |       Padding         |   |      |
|  |   |   |-------------|     |   |      |
|  |   |   |   Content   |     |   |      |
|  |   |   |-------------|     |   |      |
|  |   |-----------------------|   |      |
|  |-------------------------------|      |
|-----------------------------------------|

1.Content
-This is the actual content of the box (like text, images, etc.).
-You can set its size using width and height.
    a.height-it sets the content area height of the element
    Ex:
    div {
        height: 50px;
    }

    b.Width-it sets the content area width of the element.
    Ex:
    div {
        width: 50px;
    }
-----------------------------------------------------------------

2.Border
-It's a border surrounding the padding and content.
-It can be customized using:
    1.Width-Defines how thick the border is.
    2.Style-Defines the line pattern of the border
    3.Color-Sets the color of the border.
    4.(and also individual sides: top, right, bottom, left)
-There are two methods to write border-
1.LongHand
-Every propertyyof border is written seprately on seprate line.
Ex:
border-width: 2px;
border-style: solid;
border-color:crimson;

2.Shorthand
-All the properties of border are writte in same line only.
-Basic Syntax-
    border: [border-width] [border-style] [border-color];
-Ex:
    border: 2px solid red;

-Borde-Radius
-Used to round the corners of an element's outer border edge using two unit px or %.
-Ex:
border-radius : 10px;
border-radius : 50%;
----------------------------------------------------------------

3.Padding
-Space content of an element and its border.
-Basic YSntax:
    padding: [top] [right] [bottom] [left];
-You can set padding by two methods:
1.All sides at once
2.Each side individually
Ex:
1.padding: 20px;
2.padding-top: 10px;
  padding-right: 15px;
  padding-bottom: 20px;
  padding-left: 25px;
----------------------------------------------------------------

4.Margin
-Margin is the space outside an elementâ€™s border.
-It creates space between two elements.
-You can set margin with three types:
    1.A single value (same on all sides)
    2.Shorthand (for specific sides in one line)
    3.Each side individually (margin-top, etc.)

1.Single value
-Ex:
  margin-top: 20px;

2.Shorthand Syntax
-Syntax:
    margin: top right bottom left;
-Ex:
    margin: 10px 20px 30px 40px;

3.Individual Side Properties
-Ex:
    margin-top: 10px;
    margin-right: 20px;
    margin-bottom: 15px;
    margin-left: 25px;
